pageContext.description: Ornamented cup shaped terminals. The necks of the solid bow are ornamented with cross-hatchings, contained within lines the lower of which end in dog-tooth ornament: the inside of the cups are ornamented with a band of cross-hatchings. The presumed method by which it has been bade has been described by Mr. Edmond Johnson.*
pageContext.associations: This, with No. 278 (Plate XV) & Nos 308, 311, 307 (Plate XVI) are believed to have been discovered as above.
pageContext.publications: *Frazer and Johnson, Proc. Royal Irish Academy, XIX, pp. 781-782
